# SDS Component Usage Enforcement

- Reuse `src/components/*` for controls and text primitives whenever possible.
- Do not add local substitutes like `.btn`, custom input shells, or native checkbox styling if `Button`, `Input`, `Checkbox`, `Switch`, `Text` already cover the need.
- Prefer extending SDS components with new props/variants over creating page-local duplicates.
- Forms must be assembled from SDS form controls and state props (`default/error/disabled`, checked variants).
- All visual decisions must consume `var(--sds-*)` tokens from `src/components/theme.css`.
- If a page needs a missing component, add it to `src/components` with typed props and tokenized CSS first.

